<a name="overview"></a>
<div class="text-center text-bold text-medium bump-down-most">Dash</div>
<div class="text-left text-medium bump-down">
	The Dash provides a birds eye view of your companies financial position and 
	performance. Charts, reports and information list provide quick access to 
	information and action items such as sales tax due and late payments from customers.
</div>
<hr>

<a name="cash"></a>
<div class="text-center text-bold text-medium bump-down-most">Cash Position Report</div>
<div class="text-left text-medium bump-down">
	The Cash Position report provides a snapshot of your cash, short term debt, 
	receivables and payables so you know where cash is and how much you have at 
	any given time. The report is automatically generated from the balances of 
	account types Cash, Bank Accounts, Short Term Debt, Accounts Receivable, 
	Accounts Payable, and Pending Accounts.
</div>
<div class="text-center bump-down-most">
	<img src="/static/images/help/dash_cash.png">
</div>
<hr>


<a name="alerts"></a>
<div class="text-center text-bold text-medium bump-down-most">Alerts</div>
<div class="text-left text-medium bump-down">
	Alerts highlight payments that are coming up and actions that needs to be taken. 
	Currently, alerts will help you get started with initial task in
	BeansBooks, tell you when Sales Tax is due, and remind you when it's time to close 
	books for the year.
</div>
<div class="text-center bump-down-most">
	<img src="/static/images/help/dash_alerts.png">
</div>
<hr>


<a name="reports"></a>
<div class="text-center text-bold text-medium bump-down-most">Reports</div>
<div class="text-left text-medium bump-down">
	Reports provide insight into your business performance and the necessary information 
	for tax reporting. BeansBooks reports are automatically generated in real time as you 
	create and pay invoices and expenses.
</div>
<div class="text-center bump-down-most">
	<img src="/static/images/help/dash_reports.png">
</div>
<hr>


<a name="pastdue"></a>
<div class="text-center text-bold text-medium bump-down-most">Past Due Invoices and Payments</div>
<div class="text-left text-medium bump-down">
	The Dash provides quick access to Past Due Invoices and Past Due Payments 
	enabling you to take action on items that may have slipped through the cracks. 
	Past due status is based on the due date on the customers invoice or due date 
	when you record receipt of an invoice from a vendor.
</div>
<div class="text-center bump-down-most">
	<img src="/static/images/help/dash_pastdue.png">
</div>
<hr>


<a name="pending"></a>
<div class="text-center text-bold text-medium bump-down-most">Uninvoiced Purchase Orders and Unfulfilled Sales Orders</div>
<div class="text-left text-medium bump-down">
	BeansBooks helps you stay on top of orders and purchases by tracking uninvoiced 
	and unfulfilled orders. If you sent a Purchase Order to a vendor and haven't 
	received an invoice in 30 days, something might be wrong. This list makes it 
	easy to track those Purchase Orders and follow up with your vendor. Unfulfilled 
	Sales Orders older than thirty days list your own orders that have not been 
	invoiced yet.
</div>
<div class="text-center bump-down-most">
	<img src="/static/images/help/dash_pending.png">
</div>

